Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the Queens Museum in New York to commemorate the 70th anniversary of the United Nations vote that supported the creation of the State of Israel. He emphasized the historical significance of the vote and praised the courage and perseverance of the Jewish people. Pence reiterated President Trump's commitment to stand with Israel and emphasized the strong bond between the two countries. He also highlighted the efforts of Ambassador Nikki Haley to combat anti-Israel bias at the United Nations. Pence announced that the Trump administration is considering moving the American embassy in Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem. He assured that the United States will not allow Iran to develop a nuclear weapon and will confront the threat of radical Islamic terror. Pence concluded by expressing confidence in a brighter future for both the United States and Israel.